Definition: the quality of being inadequate or falling short of perfection
Example: they discussed the merits and demerits of her novel; he knew his own faults much better than she did
Synonyms: merit, fault, worth, the, quality, of, being, inadequate, or, falling, short, perfection, they, discussed, merits, and, demerits, her, novel, he, knew, his, own, faults, much, better, than, she, did
Category: noun.attribute
